ervasive and crucial systems, A History of Trust in Ancient Greece links Greek political, economic, social, and intellectual history in new ways and challenges contemporary analyses of trust and civil society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDemocracyzGreece. 0aTrustxEconomic aspectszGreece. 0aTrustxPolitical aspectszGreece. 0aTrustzGreecexHistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aancient world, greek, mediterranean, literature, study, academic, scholarly, history, historical, law, legal, litigation, debate, economics, economy, political, politics, social studies, communities, community, antiquity, communal, relationships, interpersonal, rhetoric, money, measurement, markets, democratic, athens, athenian, court, bc.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022640509440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226405117423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226405117/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles